{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012WAx8zMthuKF93Jn2FhNBa","type":"tool_result","content":"    87→\t\"status\": `cloche status — Check run or daemon status\n    88→\n    89→With a run ID, shows the current state of a workflow run including its\n    90→type, active step, and the result of each completed step.\n    91→\n    92→Without a run ID, shows a daemon status overview: version, run statistics,\n    93→and active runs. In a project directory, also shows project name,\n    94→concurrency, and orchestration loop state. Use --all to show global stats\n    95→instead of project-specific stats.\n    96→\n    97→Usage:\n    98→  cloche status [<run-id>] [--all]\n    99→\n   100→Arguments:\n   101→  <run-id>    The run identifier returned by \"cloche run\" (optional).\n   102→\n   103→Flags:\n   104→  --all       Show global stats instead of project-specific stats.\n   105→\n   106→Output (with run ID):\n   107→  Run         Run identifier\n   108→  Title       Human-readable title (if set)\n   109→  Workflow    Workflow name\n   110→  Type        \"host\" or \"container\"\n   111→  State       Current state (e.g. running, succeeded, failed, cancelled)\n   112→  Container   Truncated container ID (container runs only)\n   113→  Error       Error message (if failed)\n   114→  Active      Name of the currently executing step\n   115→  Steps       List of completed steps with results and timestamps\n   116→\n   117→Output (without run ID):\n   118→  Daemon version\n   119→  Project name and concurrency (if in project directory)\n   120→  Orchestration loop status\n   121→  Successful / total runs in the past hour\n   122→  Active run count with per-run duration\n   123→\n   124→Examples:\n   125→  cloche status abc123\n   126→  cloche status\n   127→  cloche status --all\n   128→`,\n   129→\n   130→\t\"logs\": `cloche logs — Show logs for a run\n   131→\n   132→Streams or displays log output for a workflow run. Supports filtering by\n   133→step name and log type, limiting output, and following live output.\n   134→\n   135→Usage:\n   136→  cloche logs <run-id> [-s <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f] [-l <n>]"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014VEUeXroYXen5wCgt1skN3","session_id":"a5729563-2c4e-4e9e-b4d2-84a0c44cd40a","uuid":"8cc6a4bf-7718-4ca3-aa42-a9d2e0f7cc1d"}
