{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QWbKZAk6m6Gq7tCzGSzyEt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Cloche MVP Implementation Plan\n     2→\n     3→> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n     4→\n     5→**Goal:** Build a working Cloche MVP — parse workflow DSL, execute steps in Docker containers, report status via gRPC.\n     6→\n     7→**Architecture:** Three Go binaries (cloche, cloched, cloche-agent) with hexagonal architecture. Domain types and DSL parser are the foundation. Build bottom-up: domain -> DSL -> engine -> agent binary -> daemon -> CLI.\n     8→\n     9→**Tech Stack:** Go 1.22+, protobuf/gRPC, Docker SDK, SQLite (via modernc.org/sqlite — pure Go), testify for assertions.\n    10→\n    11→---\n    12→\n    13→## Phase 1: Foundation\n    14→\n    15→### Task 1: Initialize Go Module and Directory Structure\n    16→\n    17→**Files:**\n    18→- Create: `go.mod`\n    19→- Create: `Makefile`\n    20→- Create: `cmd/cloche/main.go`\n    21→- Create: `cmd/cloched/main.go`\n    22→- Create: `cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`\n    23→\n    24→**Step 1: Initialize Go module**\n    25→\n    26→```bash\n    27→cd /home/lucas/workspace/cloche\n    28→go mod init github.com/cloche-dev/cloche\n    29→```\n    30→\n    31→**Step 2: Create directory structure**\n    32→\n    33→```bash\n    34→mkdir -p cmd/cloche cmd/cloched cmd/cloche-agent\n    35→mkdir -p internal/domain internal/ports\n    36→mkdir -p internal/adapters/docker internal/adapters/sqlite\n    37→mkdir -p internal/adapters/grpc internal/adapters/agents/generic\n    38→mkdir -p internal/adapters/agents/claudecode\n    39→mkdir -p internal/dsl internal/engine internal/protocol\n    40→```\n    41→\n    42→**Step 3: Create placeholder mains**\n    43→\n    44→`cmd/cloche/main.go`:\n    45→```go\n    46→package main\n    47→\n    48→func main() {}\n    49→```\n    50→\n    51→`cmd/cloched/main.go`:\n    52→```go\n    53→package main\n    54→\n    55→func main() {}\n    56→```\n    57→\n    58→`cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`:\n    59→```go\n    60→package main\n    61→\n    62→func main() {}\n    63→```\n    64→\n    65→**Step 4: Create Makefile**\n    66→\n    67→```makefile\n    68→.PHONY: build test lint clean\n    69→\n    70→build:\n    71→\tgo build -o bin/cloche ./cmd/cloche\n    72→\tgo build -o bin/cloched ./cmd/cloched\n    73→\tgo build -o bin/cloche-agent ./cmd/cloche-agent\n    74→\n    75→test:\n    76→\tgo test ./... -v\n    77→\n    78→test-short:\n    79→\tgo test ./... -short\n    80→\n    81→lint:\n    82→\tgo vet ./...\n    83→\n    84→clean:\n    85→\trm -rf bin/\n    86→```\n    87→\n    88→**Step 5: Verify build**\n    89→\n    90→```bash\n    91→make build\n    92→```\n    93→Expected: three binaries in `bin/`\n    94→\n    95→**Step 6: Commit**\n    96→\n    97→```bash\n    98→git add -A && git commit -m \"feat: initialize Go module and project structure\"\n    99→```\n   100→\n   101→---\n   102→\n   103→## Phase 2: Domain Types\n   104→\n   105→### Task 2: Workflow Domain Types\n   106→\n   107→**Files:**\n   108→- Create: `internal/domain/workflow.go`\n   109→- Create: `internal/domain/workflow_test.go`\n   110→\n   111→**Step 1: Write tests for workflow types**\n   112→\n   113→`internal/domain/workflow_test.go`:\n   114→```go\n   115→package domain_test\n   116→\n   117→import (\n   118→\t\"testing\"\n   119→\n   120→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n   121→\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/assert\"\n   122→\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/require\"\n   123→)\n   124→\n   125→func TestWorkflow_Validate_ValidGraph(t *testing.T) {\n   126→\twf := &domain.Workflow{\n   127→\t\tName: \"test-workflow\",\n   128→\t\tSteps: map[string]*domain.Step{\n   129→\t\t\t\"code\": {\n   130→\t\t\t\tName:    \"code\",\n   131→\t\t\t\tType:    domain.StepTypeAgent,\n   132→\t\t\t\tResults: []string{\"success\", \"fail\"},\n   133→\t\t\t},\n   134→\t\t\t\"check\": {\n   135→\t\t\t\tName:    \"check\",\n   136→\t\t\t\tType:    domain.StepTypeScript,\n   137→\t\t\t\tResults: []string{\"pass\", \"fail\"},\n   138→\t\t\t},\n   139→\t\t},\n   140→\t\tWiring: []domain.Wire{\n   141→\t\t\t{From: \"code\", Result: \"success\", To: \"check\"},\n   142→\t\t\t{From: \"code\", Result: \"fail\", To: domain.StepAbort},\n   143→\t\t\t{From: \"check\", Result: \"pass\", To: domain.StepDone},\n   144→\t\t\t{From: \"check\", Result: \"fail\", To: \"code\"},\n   145→\t\t},\n   146→\t\tEntryStep: \"code\",\n   147→\t}\n   148→\n   149→\terr := wf.Validate()\n   150→\tassert.NoError(t, err)\n   151→}\n   152→\n   153→func TestWorkflow_Validate_UnwiredResult(t *testing.T) {\n   154→\twf := &domain.Workflow{\n   155→\t\tName: \"test-workflow\",\n   156→\t\tSteps: map[string]*domain.Step{\n   157→\t\t\t\"code\": {\n   158→\t\t\t\tName:    \"code\",\n   159→\t\t\t\tType:    domain.StepTypeAgent,\n   160→\t\t\t\tResults: []string{\"success\", \"fail\"},\n   161→\t\t\t},\n   162→\t\t},\n   163→\t\tWiring: []domain.Wire{\n   164→\t\t\t{From: \"code\", Result: \"success\", To: domain.StepDone},\n   165→\t\t\t// \"fail\" is not wired\n   166→\t\t},\n   167→\t\tEntryStep: \"code\",\n   168→\t}\n   169→\n   170→\terr := wf.Validate()\n   171→\trequire.Error(t, err)\n   172→\tassert.Contains(t, err.Error(), \"fail\")\n   173→}\n   174→\n   175→func TestWorkflow_Validate_OrphanStep(t *testing.T) {\n   176→\twf := &domain.Workflow{\n   177→\t\tName: \"test-workflow\",\n   178→\t\tSteps: map[string]*domain.Step{\n   179→\t\t\t\"code\": {\n   180→\t\t\t\tName:    \"code\",\n   181→\t\t\t\tType:    domain.StepTypeAgent,\n   182→\t\t\t\tResults: []string{\"success\"},\n   183→\t\t\t},\n   184→\t\t\t\"orphan\": {\n   185→\t\t\t\tName:    \"orphan\",\n   186→\t\t\t\tType:    domain.StepTypeScript,\n   187→\t\t\t\tResults: []string{\"done\"},\n   188→\t\t\t},\n   189→\t\t},\n   190→\t\tWiring: []domain.Wire{\n   191→\t\t\t{From: \"code\", Result: \"success\", To: domain.StepDone},\n   192→\t\t\t{From: \"orphan\", Result: \"done\", To: domain.StepDone},\n   193→\t\t},\n   194→\t\tEntryStep: \"code\",\n   195→\t}\n   196→\n   197→\terr := wf.Validate()\n   198→\trequire.Error(t, err)\n   199→\tassert.Contains(t, err.Error(), \"orphan\")\n   200→}"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014VEUeXroYXen5wCgt1skN3","session_id":"a5729563-2c4e-4e9e-b4d2-84a0c44cd40a","uuid":"5fef809b-4de2-4577-aedc-695e51119aee"}
